Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets. Halve any large florets.
Pop into a #mixing bowl{}. Add half the @aioli{1%sachet} and toss to coat.
In a separate #bowl{}, mix the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and
@oil{1%tbsp}. Add the breadcrumb mix to the bowl and toss to coat evenly.

Pop the coated broccoli onto a lined #baking tray{} and arrange in a single
layer—well spaced out. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until
golden and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If the florets don't fit in a single spaced out layer spread them across
> two baking trays.

Meanwhile, add @water{300%ml}(cold) to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}. Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid. Cook for ~{12%minutes},
then remove the pot from the heat. Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or
until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice
widthways into 1cm thick pieces.

Trim half the @cucumber{1/2} and halve lengthways then thinly slice widthways.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{2}. Separate the green portions from the
white.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Once hot,
fry the carrot until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @soy sauce{1%sachet} and the
whites of the scallion and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the pan from the
heat and cover to keep the veg warm. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

To make the bang bang sauce, combine @red wine vinegar{1/2%sachet}, the
@sweet chilli sauce{2%sachets} and the remaining @aioli{1%sachet} in a bowl.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{}.
Top with crispy broccoli, fried veg and sliced cucumber. Finish with a
drizzle of bang bang sauce and a sprinkling of green scallion.